          <text>
            <table xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
              <thead><tr><th>Date</th><th>Provider</th><th>Note Type</th><th>Note Text</th><th>Location</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td>03/10/2026</td><td>Cory Denton, FNP</td><td>Progress Note</td><td>CC: Follow-up DM, HTN, CKD
HPI: 72yo female presents for chronic disease management. Reports good medication compliance. Occasional HA in mornings. Denies chest pain, SOB, edema.
A1c improved to 7.8% from 8.2%. Creatinine stable at 1.6. eGFR 38 (Stage 3b CKD). BP elevated today 142/88.
Assessment:
# Type 2 DM (E11.9): A1c trending down. Continue metformin 1000mg BID.
# HTN (I10): Suboptimal control. Increase amlodipine to 10mg daily.
# CKD Stage 3 (N18.3): Stable. Continue ACE inhibitor. Recheck BMP in 3 months.
# Osteoporosis (M81.0): Continue alendronate. DEXA due 2027.
# Depression (F33.1): PHQ-9 = 8 (mild). Stable on sertraline 100mg.
Plan: Labs in 3 months. RTC 3 months. Shingrix dose 2 due. Discussed colon cancer screening — patient will schedule colonoscopy.</td><td>Family Practice Associates of Chesterfield</td></tr>
                <tr><td>12/15/2025</td><td>Cory Denton, FNP</td><td>Progress Note</td><td>CC: Chronic disease follow-up
HPI: Reports increased fatigue, occasional nocturia x2. No dysuria. Diet compliance fair — admits to holiday indulgences.
A1c 7.5%. BP 148/92. Weight up 2 lbs.
Assessment:
# DM2: A1c slightly improved. Reinforce dietary counseling.
# HTN: Adding HCTZ 12.5mg. Monitor K+ in 2 weeks.
# CKD: Urine albumin/creat ratio 55 — microalbuminuria. Continue ACE.
# Depression: Stable. PHQ-9 = 6.
Plan: BMP + K in 2 weeks. Follow-up 3 months.</td><td>Family Practice Associates of Chesterfield</td></tr>
                <tr><td>01/05/2026</td><td>Patricia Lavinus, NP</td><td>Acute Visit</td><td>CC: Dysuria x 3 days, urgency, frequency
HPI: 72yo with h/o CKD presents with UTI symptoms. No fever, no flank pain.
UA: Positive nitrites, leukocyte esterase 3+, bacteria many. Culture sent.
Assessment: Uncomplicated UTI (N39.0) in setting of CKD.
Plan: Nitrofurantoin 100mg BID x 5 days (renal-dose appropriate for eGFR >30). Increase fluids. Follow-up if not improved in 48 hours.</td><td>Family Practice Associates of Chesterfield</td></tr>
                <tr><td>09/15/2025</td><td>Cory Denton, FNP</td><td>Annual Wellness Visit</td><td>ANNUAL WELLNESS VISIT (AWV) — G0439
HPI: 72yo female here for AWV. No acute complaints.
Preventive Review:
- Mammogram: Last 01/2024. Due 01/2025 — OVERDUE
- Colonoscopy: Last 2018. Due 2028 (or stool test annually) — OVERDUE for stool test
- Bone Density: Last 2022. Next due 2024 — Schedule DEXA
- Lung Cancer Screen: Former smoker 20 pack-years, quit <15 years ago. ELIGIBLE for LDCT
- Depression Screen: PHQ-9 completed today = 6
- Fall Risk: Timed Up and Go = 12 seconds (normal)
- Cognitive: Mini-Cog normal
- Advance Directive: Completed, copy in chart
Vaccines: Flu given today. Shingrix dose 2 needed (dose 1 was 06/2024).
Plan: Order mammogram, FIT test, DEXA scan, LDCT chest. RTC 3 months for chronic disease f/u.</td><td>Family Practice Associates of Chesterfield</td></tr>
